    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 60.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Continuing the subject of former correspondence,
                    the delivery of the shares in the Banque Nationale and of the unified scrip, I
                    have the honor to report that the minister of finance has notified me that this
                    Government would accept them. * * *</p>
                <p>Accordingly, on October 21 I delivered the said shares and scrip to Amadeo
                    Rodriguez, contador-general, who was empowered to receive them on behalf of the
                    Dominican Government, taking from him receipts and also the document releasing
                    the San Domingo Improvement Company and its allied companies, which had been
                    sent by Mr. Abbott as inclosue in his letter to the minister of finance of
                    October 7.</p>
                <p>Neither Mr. Abbott, attorney for the companies, nor myself saw <pb facs="0373"
                        n="285" xml:id="pg_285"/> any reason why I should not comply with Minister
                    Lamarche’s request that I receive the shares and bonds back from the Dominican
                    Government and keep them as its depositary. This Government will probably not
                    ask for them until the termination of the negotiations it proposes to initiate
                    looking toward a modification of the award.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. C. Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
